# Lesson 2-1 — Polygon Basics & Angle Sums

## Today's Goals

* Use the polygon angle sum theorem to find the sum of interior angles of any polygon
* Find each interior angle of a regular polygon
* Relate exterior angles of polygons to their sum and individual measures

---

## Vocabulary

* **polygon** — a closed figure formed by three or more line segments that intersect only at their endpoints
* **regular polygon** — a polygon with all sides congruent and all angles congruent
* **interior angle** — an angle formed inside a polygon by two adjacent sides
* **exterior angle** — an angle formed outside a polygon by one side and the extension of an adjacent side
* **polygon angle sum theorem** — the sum of the interior angles of an n-gon is $(n - 2) \times 180°$
* **exterior angle sum theorem** — the sum of the exterior angles of any convex polygon is 360°

